CBRE is pleased to offer for sale De Mole Estate, a world-class and iconic holding located on the pristine Kangaroo Island.

Comprising a spectacular 2,398* hectare estate with over three kilometres of stunning coastline, De Mole Estate has long been used in South Australian tourism campaigns to promote the natural beauty of Kangaroo Island to the rest of the world.

Offered for the first time in almost 50 years, De Mole Estate is in the secluded north-west corner of Kangaroo Island and features 61 Certificates of Title, along with approximately 3.7 kilometres of private coastline, including sandy beaches and rugged cliffs overlooking the Indian Ocean. 

The coveted estate represents a prime development opportunity for international corporate investors or high net worth individuals seeking to capitalise on the global tourism appeal of Kangaroo Island, which earlier this year was ranked in the world’s top three travel destinations by Lonely Planet.

Key features of De Mole Estate include:

• A flagship 2,398* hectare contiguous landholding, comprising 61 Certificates of Title, in one of Australia’s most scenic locations.

• Over three kilometres of stunning coastline and private access to Kangaroo Beach, ideal for snorkelling, fishing, swimming and whale watching. 

• Breathtaking landscape and natural environment that includes Fides Bluff, Whale Gully, Coveny’s Gully and De Mole Beach. 

• Passive income of $50,000* per annum from a lease in place with a livestock grazing enterprise. 

• A unique development opportunity (Subject to Council Approval) in an internationally acclaimed tourism destination.

• Structural improvements include a homestead, shearing shed, hay shed, several machinery / storage sheds and cattle and sheep yards. 



*approximately

CBRE Agribusiness is pleased to present for sale Mount Schanck Station, one of South Australia’s most renowned and outstanding properties, currently operated as a highly productive livestock enterprise.

Comprising approximately 2,866* hectares, Mount Schanck Station is ideally located only 13* lineal kilometres south of Mount Gambier, a key regional centre and transportation hub with a focus on the Australian agriculture industry.

Key features of Mount Schanck Station include:

- A large scale, contiguous landholding comprising improved pastures, outstanding soil types and well-developed infrastructure, underpinned by excellent climatic conditions (average annual rainfall of 745* millimetres).

- Approximately 690* hectares has been developed to 11 centre pivot irrigators, benefited by a 5,000* megalitre Ground Water Entitlement, with significant scope for further irrigation development.

- A highly productive grazing enterprise comprising both cattle and sheep, with an estimated carrying capacity of over 60,000* Dry Sheep Equivalents (DSE) at its current level of development, with capacity for further development.

- Located close to the Port of Portland (87* lineal kilometres), saleyards at Mount Gambier (13* lineal kilometres) and Hamilton (113* lineal kilometres) and processing facilities at Warrnambool (158* lineal kilometres).

- Stunning Mount Schanck Homestead (circa 1864, renovated 1986), featuring four bedrooms and set within manicured gardens, open lawn areas and garden beds providing ideal entertaining areas and a luxurious country lifestyle. Further accommodation includes numerous additional high quality staff residences.

- Operational infrastructure including a circa 1875 6-stand shearing shed, "as new" Pratley sheep and cattle yards and various machinery / hay / implement / storage sheds.

- Farm infrastructure, including a well-designed laneway system, high quality fencing and excellent stock water facilities.
